org.sopra.api.model

Interface EnergyNode

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    BioGasFiredPowerPlant, City, CoalFiredPowerPlant, CommercialPark, Consumer, ControllableConsumer, ControllableProducer, GasFiredPowerPlant, HydroPowerPlant, IndustrialPark, NuclearPowerPlant, Producer, SolarPowerPlant, TransformerStation, WindPowerPlant

    public interface EnergyNode
    Nodes in a scenario graph. These node represent actual places on the map. Therefore, they need a name and coordinates. The meaning of the energy level of an EnergyNode is dependent on the dynamic type of the node. If it is a consumer, the energy level is the amount of energy currently consumed. If it is a producer, it is the amount of produced energy. The maximum energy level has a similar meaning. It depicts the maximum amount of energy production/consumption, this node is capable of.
